http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/bangalore/College-to-rename-block-after-martyr/article14019846.ece

On Republic Day, a city-based engineering college will pay a tribute to a martyr by renaming one of its blocks after him.New Horizon College of Engineering will rename a block, which will serve as a recreation centre for students, after Lt. Col. Niranjan E. Kumar, the NSG commando who lost his life in agrenade blast in the recent Pathankot terror attack in Punjab.The renamed block will be inaugurated by Lt. Col. Niranjan's father K. Shivarajan.Lt. Col. Niranjan, whose father is a retired employee of Bharat Electronics Limited (BEL), was born in Bengaluru and completed his studies here.